&lt;h2 id="everything-feels-alive">Everything Feels Alive
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Apple makes apps built with their frameworks (specifically the Cocoa frameworks,) feel alive. When an app on
the Mac needs attention, it jumps at you as if it were to say, &amp;ldquo;Look at me! Right here!&amp;rdquo; and on the iPhone,
activities in the Dynamic Island will expand, analogous to someone bursting into your office to tell you
something urgent.&lt;/p>
